ilog.cp

Enum IloCP.Callback.Reason

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<IloCP.Callback.Reason>
      • ilog.cp.IloCP.Callback.Reason
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<IloCP.Callback.Reason>
    Enclosing interface:
    IloCP.Callback

    public static enum IloCP.Callback.Reason
extends java.lang.Enum<IloCP.Callback.Reason>

    This enumerated type comprises the different reasons for which a user callback can be invoked. An argument of this type is passed to IloCP.Callback.invoke(ilog.cp.IloCP, ilog.cp.IloCP.Callback.Reason). You can use it to control the behavior of your callback.
